comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/benheine] see more great images here... www.jeffcarterphotos.com/?cat=rural I just came across a little cafe in Berry on the New South Wales south coast on Sunday, I was photographing some of the places mentioned in David Astle's book, "Offbeat Australia", and found the "Hedgehogs" cafe mentioned on p.111 I have created a group on Flickr for members to post their images of all the places mentioned in the book... www.flickr.com/groups/1331432@N25/ I popped into the cafe to tell them they were mentioned in the Offbeat book, and the manager was most interested. Around the walls of the cafe were many Jeff Carter images, and copies of his books, one is out of print... "Jeff Carter, Retrospective". I took several photos around the shop and in the street, which I will load soon to Flickr. The friendly chap in charge, Van, turned out to be Jeff's son...... Www.hedgehogscoffeeshop.com.au
